commitResults.messageBody:
Some methods are too long and some are no longer used. Proper coding
standards are also not being adhered to in some parts.

These methods may hinder code readability making it harder for other
people to understand certain parts of the code.

Let's,
* remove methods/ classes no longer in use
* refactor long methods
* adhere to coding standard

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions
commitResults.messageBody:
Index of task to get is not checked.

Invalid index results in program crashing.

Checking the index before passing it to get() allows us to pass an
error message to the user instead of crashing the pogram.

Let's assert the index to make sure it is valid before passing it to
get().

Using assert allows us to document the assumption that index is valid.
